      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Global Climate Gamble</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Fuoss letter holds we should discuss ethics and humility of Pres Bush's policy of forcing costs of global warming on world</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Since the costs of global warming fall mainly on other countries, President Bush's gamble should be characterized ''heads we win, tails they lose'' (''Climate Plan Is Criticized'').</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Since the costs of global warming fall mainly on other countries, President Bush's gamble should be characterized ''heads we win, tails they lose'' (''Climate Plan Is Criticized'').</p>
        <p>Perhaps we should discuss the ethics and humility of forcing that bet on the world.</p>
        <p>PAUL FUOSS  Woodridge, Ill.</p>
      </block>
